00:30:17.851 --> 00:30:20.100
You've had a good time, if
you can remember any of it.

00:30:20.100 --> 00:30:23.900
And it gives life
a sense of meaning.

00:30:23.900 --> 00:30:26.530
But you don't come back from
it with a whole bunch of stuff,

00:30:26.530 --> 00:30:27.030
do you?

00:30:27.030 --> 00:30:28.350
Hopefully, you've lost stuff.

00:30:28.350 --> 00:30:30.690
Anyway, so just to
be really clear.

00:30:30.690 --> 00:30:33.130
So in terms of what I
mean by experiences,

00:30:33.130 --> 00:30:37.970
is that which is something
where you're doing something

00:30:37.970 --> 00:30:39.250
rather than having something.

00:30:39.250 --> 00:30:41.100
That's the kind of
classic distinction.

00:30:41.100 --> 00:30:45.710
There's two psychologists--
called [INAUDIBLE]

00:30:45.710 --> 00:30:50.760
and Tom Gilovich-- and they had
a paper they published in 2003

00:30:50.760 --> 00:30:51.920
called, "To Do or To Have?

00:30:51.920 --> 00:30:53.400
That Is the Question."

00:30:53.400 --> 00:30:55.230
And it was-- it is--
considered to be

00:30:55.230 --> 00:30:59.200
the kind of classic
moment in research.

00:30:59.200 --> 00:31:02.250
To find, for the first
time, whether material goods

00:31:02.250 --> 00:31:04.310
or experiential goods gave
people more happiness.

00:31:04.310 --> 00:31:05.810
And they proved,
for the first time,

00:31:05.810 --> 00:31:08.500
that experiential goods
gave people more happiness.

00:31:08.500 --> 00:31:10.910
But to begin that
piece of research,

00:31:10.910 --> 00:31:13.524
they started by saying,
what's a material good?

00:31:13.524 --> 00:31:14.690
What's an experiential good?

00:31:14.690 --> 00:31:18.800
Because for some people, a TV is
experiential, and some people,

00:31:18.800 --> 00:31:20.000
it's material.

00:31:20.000 --> 00:31:22.710
Just to be really clear,
this is not anti-consumerist,

00:31:22.710 --> 00:31:26.170
it's not anti-capitalists,
it's not even anti stuff.

00:31:26.170 --> 00:31:30.470
It's totally pro
consumers, pro capitalist,

00:31:30.470 --> 00:31:31.760
and it's not anti stuff.

00:31:31.760 --> 00:31:33.710
It's having stuff.

00:31:33.710 --> 00:31:35.850
We bought a bread maker
a couple of weeks ago.

00:31:35.850 --> 00:31:38.710
Now that has got the potential
to be a waste of money.

00:31:38.710 --> 00:31:40.750
But my wife insists
that we will use it--

00:31:40.750 --> 00:31:42.610
and we fully intend
to-- in which case,

00:31:42.610 --> 00:31:44.320
it's got use, right?

00:31:44.320 --> 00:31:45.870
So it's not anti
having stuff, it's

00:31:45.870 --> 00:31:49.299
anti having too much stuff.

00:31:49.299 --> 00:31:50.590
Does that answer your question?

00:31:50.590 --> 00:31:51.250
AUDIENCE: That does.

00:31:51.250 --> 00:31:51.770
Yeah.

