00:32:54.390 --> 00:32:57.694
They were just happy
doing what they did.

00:32:57.694 --> 00:33:01.140
JAMES WALLMAN: I'd really like
to give a good answer generally

00:33:01.140 --> 00:33:02.640
but I don't know
if I have an answer

00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:07.330
because I think having loads of
possibilities-- I mean, boredom

00:33:07.330 --> 00:33:08.862
is your own
responsibility, right?

00:33:08.862 --> 00:33:10.820
It comes to the weekend
and you've got a choice

00:33:10.820 --> 00:33:13.740
of-- especially where
you guys live, right?--

00:33:13.740 --> 00:33:16.140
there's so many outdoor
activities you can do.

00:33:16.140 --> 00:33:19.252
Or you can go to San Francisco.

00:33:19.252 --> 00:33:20.710
I mean, the world's,
kind of, here.

00:33:20.710 --> 00:33:22.680
There's so many
things we can do now.

00:33:22.680 --> 00:33:24.520
I think being bored is terrible.

00:33:24.520 --> 00:33:27.144
And if you're bored of your job,
you should do a different job.

00:33:27.144 --> 00:33:29.550
I, personally, am
infused by my job.

00:33:29.550 --> 00:33:31.960
And it's been my
experience of the people

00:33:31.960 --> 00:33:34.370
that I-- I was in New
York for a few days,

00:33:34.370 --> 00:33:36.480
I've now been here in
