00:34:23.073 --> 00:34:24.489
JAMES WALLMAN:
Well you can become

00:34:24.489 --> 00:34:25.892
a kind of zombie consumer.

00:34:25.892 --> 00:34:27.350
You just buy more
stuff because you

00:34:27.350 --> 00:34:29.120
think it's going
to solve problems.

00:34:29.120 --> 00:34:31.300
You're going to turn
to retail therapy.

00:34:31.300 --> 00:34:33.150
But that's the truth
about retail therapy,

00:34:33.150 --> 00:34:35.650
in terms of buying stuff, it
won't make you any happier.

00:34:35.650 --> 00:34:37.960
But if you buy an
experiential good,

00:34:37.960 --> 00:34:40.949
like going on a rock
climbing course,

00:34:40.949 --> 00:34:44.250
you'll be so scared you
won't be able to be bored.

00:34:44.250 --> 00:34:46.449
So if you're bored, go
rock climbing, or skiing,

00:34:46.449 --> 00:34:47.159
or surfing.

00:34:47.159 --> 00:34:49.125
That's frightening, too.

00:34:49.125 --> 00:34:52.530
AUDIENCE: What's different
